<div type="original">
<ab><pb f="1r" facs="#zone-pb-1r-1" n="1" xml:id="pb-original-1r-1" /></ab>
<ab>Mijnheer,</ab><lb n="1*" xml:id="l-1s" />
<ab>Of ik Zaturdag a.s. kan komen schilderen <lb n="2" xml:id="l-2" />weet ik niet zeker<c type="kp">_</c>– Omdat ik een paar studies aan <lb n="3" xml:id="l-3" />’t maken ben hier – van het aardappelzetten<anchor n="1" xml:id="note-o-1" /> – <lb n="4" xml:id="l-4" />waar ik dien dag in kwestie welligt aan zal moeten <lb n="5" xml:id="l-5" />blijven werken.</ab><lb n="6" xml:id="l-6" />
<ab rend="indent">Doch indien niet Zaturdag dan kom ik toch – <lb n="7" xml:id="l-7" />tenzij in geval van tegenberigt uwerzijds – <lb n="8" xml:id="l-8" />Maandag.</ab>
<ns1:whiteline /><lb n="9" xml:id="l-9" />
<ab>b. à v.</ab><lb n="10" xml:id="l-10" />
<ab>Vincent</ab>
<ns1:whiteline /><figure facs="zone-sketch-1" n="A" />
<ns1:whiteline />
    <ab><pb f="1v" facs="#zone-pb-1v-2" n="1" xml:id="pb-orig-1v-2" /></ab>
<div type="textualNotes">
</div></div>
<div type="translation">
<ab><pb f="1r" facs="#zone-pb-1r-1" n="1" xml:id="pb-trans-1r-1" /></ab>
<ab>Dear <rs key="475" type="pers">Sir</rs>,</ab>
<ab>I’m not sure whether I can come and paint next Saturday. Because I’m making a couple of studies here — of the potato planting<anchor n="1" xml:id="note-t-1" /> — on which I may possibly have to continue to work on the day in question.</ab>
<ab rend="indent">But if not Saturday, I’ll come anyway — unless I hear from you to the contrary — on Monday.</ab>
<ns1:whiteline />
<ab>Yours truly,</ab>
<ab>Vincent</ab>
<ns1:whiteline />
<ab><figure facs="zone-sketch-1" n="A" /></ab>
    <ab><pb f="1v" facs="#zone-pb-1v-2" n="1" xml:id="pb-trans-1v-2" /></ab>
</div>
        
<div type="notes">
<note n="1" target="#note-t-1" xml:id="n-1">
    <ab>One of these studies is still extant: <hi rend="ital">Man and a woman planting potatoes</hi> (<rs key="2503" type="ill">F 129a / JH 727</rs>), after which the letter sketch of the same name was made (<rs key="144" type="sketch">F - / JH 728</rs>). The composition of the other one is now known only from <hi rend="ital">Two women working in the fields </hi>(<rs key="145" type="sketch">F 1228 / JH 730</rs>), the sketch enclosed with <ref target="let492.xml">letter 492</ref>.</ab></note></div></body></text></TEI>